  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or bank accounts. Typical legal definitions include:\n\n1. Core elements typically include:\n- Concealing the source of illicit funds\n- Transforming illegal money into seemingly legal assets\n- Attempting to make criminal proceeds appear legitimate\n\n2. Key legal components often involve:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds derive from criminal activity\n- Attempting to disguise the origin of funds\n\n3. Most jurisdictions recognize three main stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (complex transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (funds reintroduced as seemingly legitimate)\n\n4. Specific criminal statutes vary by country, but generally include:\n- Intentional financial transfers\n- Structured transactions to avoid reporting requirements\n- Concealing ownership or source of funds\n\n5. Typical predicate crimes include:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Illegal gambling\n- Terrorist financing\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
